---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About Me"
	description="Full-stack web developer focused on Ruby on Rails, React, APIs, dashboards, and practical software that solves real business problems."
	pubDate={new Date('May 05 2026')}
	heroImage="/img/profile-picture.jpg**"
>
	<div class="flex flex-col gap-6">
		<p class="block">
			I’m Diego Vidal Lopez, a full-stack web developer from Villahermosa, Tabasco, Mexico. I build
			practical software for real problems: internal tools, dashboards, APIs, automations, and web
			systems that help teams work better.
		</p>

		<p class="block">
			My main stack includes Ruby on Rails, JavaScript, React, PostgreSQL, Tailwind CSS, and modern
			development workflows. I enjoy working across the backend and frontend, from designing business
			logic and database models to building clear interfaces that people can actually use.
		</p>

		<p class="block">
			What I enjoy most is taking a messy, manual, or repetitive process and turning it into something
			clear, reliable, and useful. I like understanding how a business works, finding the parts that
			create friction, and building software that saves time, reduces mistakes, and gives people better
			visibility into their work.
		</p>

		<p class="block">
			My path into software has been shaped by curiosity, resilience, and constant learning. I taught
			myself English to access global opportunities, learned to work remotely, and built projects across
			frontend and backend technologies. That experience taught me to be adaptable, disciplined, and
			focused on delivering value.
		</p>

		<p class="block">
			I’m especially interested in Ruby on Rails, business applications, backend logic, APIs,
			dashboards, financial tools, automation, and systems that help companies operate more efficiently.
			I care about clean code, but I care even more about useful software that survives production and
			helps real people.
		</p>

		<p class="block">
			I’m always learning, always improving, and always looking for better ways to build. If you’re
			looking for someone who can help build, improve, or automate a web system, I’d be happy to
			connect.
		</p>
	</div>
</Layout>